                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Let me start out by saying that I am not a hardcore player. I dont have time to be. Yet every time I have played since the change happened I have hit my well rested limit. I have two characters roughly the same level because of it. I never have two characters. I've explored everything within my level range, I have even done tradeskills. I made some friends, joined a guild. I by no means have been idle.
<br />
Oh and the best part of all this is that I played all last night with my husband grouped and he hit his cap a full level faster then I did. Brilliant I tell you.
<br />
If they do choose this option as a solution for..something...I'm really not sure what this is supposed to be a solution for..then they have to up the well rested cap quite a bit. 
<br />
All this cap does it encourage people to play EVERY day for the max amount of time. Lots of people that I know only get to play a few days a week, but they play as long as they can. Is this hardcore? No. And yet these are the people that are getting screwed by this random rule. 
<br />
And what really is this fixing? Nothing. If I play more then my husband we are going to be different levels no matter what. So it may take a little longer but it will happen none the less.
<br />
Its there to encourage the well rounded character. Hmmm, I think not. Socialising is something that is done while playing the game, not just while your sitting arround in the tavern resting.
<br />
Tradeskills maybe? Again most tradeskills are done while playing the game. You run arround and come accross a flower to pick while your doing X quest. Its something that happens while playing.
<br />
Oh the camping issue might be fixed by this. Again I dont think so. If you are camping something (taking an EQ view here for a sec) your not interested in the exp anyway. Besides in WoW they are trying to not do the camping thing, although its not working too great due to overpopulation atm. The main reason things are camped in EQ is to camp for items. Items in WoW are random drops, quest rewards and crafted. If you really need to "camp" something for a quest then again the exp for killing the mob is not the main factor at hand. The resting thing is an exp penalty, no more. 
<br />
The only thing I could see it effecting is the "grinders". The people that only kill monsters for exp, and dont do the quests. But we now seem to be getting more exp per mob so I'm not sure if thats even it. 
<br />
I'm just not sure I see the point in this rule at all. It seems to be just a nuisance.
<br />

<br />
Okay [/ramble]
<br />
 <img src="images/smiles/icon_rolleyes.gif" alt="icon_rolleyes.gif" border="0" /></span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
                        </tr>
