                        <tr>
                                <td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Let me first start by saying that I am not in the WoW beta, though I applied to be.  
<br />

<br />
Let me also say that I am someone who likes to make the most out of my playing time.  I play any game I am interested in a lot.  Unfortunately, playing time != progress in EQ right now, hence one of the reasons I am following WoW so closely.
<br />

<br />
It seems to me that they're simply trying to get people to do other things.  The quest XP is not affected at all, and I am reading on several boards, including WoW's beta forums that the quest xp is very good in general.  Also, I read something about skill points and how they only come from xp'ing on mobs.  So if you level with quests, you gain no skill points.  
<br />

<br />
Sounds like they are doing everything in their "test" power to try and get people to experience the "game" and not just powergaming.  Everyone wants to make the most "efficient" use of their time.  Some people consider getting xp every second while online to be the most efficient method.  Others are very happy with doing "something", meaning exploring, tradeskilling, questing, etc.  My wife loves questing, hence she despises EQ now. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />  I like making progress in whatever goal I currently have (usually xp for AAs now), and exploring.
<br />

<br />
Sounds like a "yes" they are unfairly penalizing people who can play, as an example, on Saturday and Sunday only but for 12 hours each day.  BUT... it also sounds like these people will not have a problem leveling.  They will simply have to level through quests, or switch characters (I normally play 2-3 in any given game myself due to my like of different experiences).  Also, breaking the well rested barrier definitely lowers your xp, but it brings the xp back to what the monsters are normally worth.  There are 5 fatigue levels... well rested is a bonus level thrown in there for those people with the absolute minimum time to hunt.  Well rested gives MORE xp than what was achieved before.  Say well rested lasts for 2 hours (that seems like a lot), then normal for 3-4, then fatigued for 2 and then the last one is entered.  Well, that would mean you need 8 hours of rest (a good night's sleep), in order to get back to well rested.  
<br />

<br />
If you're like me, you'll hunt through the well rested and rested phases, keep going if you're having a good time, or just leave after the rested phase and go questing and tradeskilling.   Or, honestly, go play one of my alts. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="icon_smile.gif" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
Also, this is still beta.  They may have thrown this in there in the hopes that everyone in beta will now have a reason to try all quests, all tradeskills, etc.  This is Blizzard.  They change a lot from beta to release in every game.  They change things just for beta.  They test games well and release some of the least problematic titles in the industry.  I'm willing to give them the benefit of the doubt on this one.  
<br />

<br />
The skill point issue seems odd, as it means that you can level faster by questing and hunting than hunting alone, but gain more skill points by hunting alone (technically).  The one thing about this is that skill points are locked in at a fixed xp rate (like 1 skill point every 600xp).  Which means that as you level higher, skill points come faster.  So it sounds like going through questing at the early levels is the way to go for fast leveling (I hate the first few levels of any game usually and despise EQ until 20).  After the levels are gained, you can gain skill points faster, and THEN you'll have to worry about the rested state much more if you're focused on skill points.  
<br />

<br />
As long as they have only a hard cap on xp earned towards level and not towards skill points though, it all comes out square in the end.  AND questing is a very viable way to xp while you're resting.  
<br />

<br />
I expect this game to be nothing like EQ.  EQ (everqamp) broke itself long ago.  But that's a story for another thread.  
<br />

<br />
Have a good day all, and if anyone in beta has any news on them giving out more beta accounts, please let me know.
<br />

<br />
Aerdyn
<br />
65 ench on BB</span><span class="postbody"></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
