<br />

<br />
I think there is an underlying impression here that there are significant issues with a system like EQ which is simple time economics: the more time you spend, the more benefit you'll receive.  In spite of some of the arguments you've made about play time, I don't think there is a problem.  In addition, I think resting prohibits people from playing and consequently, not beneficial.  
<br />

<br />
If resting is allowed to live, then this game will not cater to developing a single "main" character.  Instead it will force people who enjoy playing a particular class to play something they would not necessarily enjoy.  How is that fun?
<br />

<br />
</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Twizlewink wrote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote"> So what's the issue for the power gamer? Why not simply have multiple high level charecters? Perhaps different races or class? Or just a different race and the same class? </td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
Think about this for a second. Suppose I play around 30-40 hours a week which would require me to have at least 3 toons on a given day.  Now I end up having to do three times the work... grinding, questing, raiding, tradeskills -- you name it.  When I end up having to repeat something over and over again, monotony sets in and frankly that's no fun...especially so when I end up repeating something for multiple toons that I made merely to fill time up and not necessarily for enjoyment.
<br />

<br />
Another angle... Lets suppose they introduce high end content which requires quite a bit of time spent playing to accomplish something in particular.  Because of the resting policy, this means that no raid content can be longer than a specific duration (i think right now resting is required after 4 hours??).  I know my guild is doing Time in about 5 hours... GOD encounters can take up to 6 hours...  With this time limit, now what do we do when all of our tanks and healers are too "tired" and we're 3/4 of the way through?</span><span class="postbody"><br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=406237" target="_blank" class="postlink">Baalazai</a>
<br />
